{#- ═══ CALC ISLAND — the .calc widget markup is preserved VERBATIM (the select-
    formula JS binds to data-calc / data-select-formula / data-calc-sel / data-out
    — class restyle on the result CTA only is behavior-safe). id="calc" kept so the
    hero "Skip to the calculator" anchor still lands. ═══ -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="calc">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">The calculator</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:24ch;margin-bottom:10px;">Find your filing deadline.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:66ch;">Pick the tax year &mdash; the year the income was paid. The deadline shown is for filing in the following year.</p>

    <div class="calc" data-calc data-select-formula="deadline">
      <form class="calc__form" aria-describedby="calc-disclaimer-top">
        <p class="calc__formnote" id="calc-disclaimer-top">Published IRS rules &mdash; confirm current-year dates on IRS.gov.</p>
        <div class="calc__field intake-field">
          <label class="intake-field__label" for="sel-year">Tax year <span class="intake-field__optional">year the income was paid</span></label>
          <select id="sel-year" data-calc-sel="year">
            <option value="2024">2024 (filed in 2025)</option>
            <option value="2025">2025 (filed in 2026)</option>
            <option value="2026">2026 (filed in 2027)</option>
            <option value="2027">2027 (filed in 2028)</option>
          </select>
        </div>
      </form>

      <div class="calc__result" id="calc-result" role="status" aria-live="polite">
        <p class="calc__result-label">1099-NEC &amp; W-2 deadline</p>
        <p class="calc__result-range"><span data-out="primary">&mdash;</span></p>
        <ul class="calc__metrics">
          <li class="calc__metric"><span class="calc__metric-label">1099-MISC e-file to IRS</span><span class="calc__metric-value" data-out="m1">&mdash;</span></li>
        </ul>
        <p class="calc__result-why" data-out="text">Pick a tax year above to see the deadline.</p>
        <p class="calc__result-disclaimer">These are the published federal rules &mdash; <strong>always confirm the exact current-year dates on IRS.gov</strong>. State deadlines and penalties may differ, and this is general information, not tax advice.</p>
        <a class="btn btn-cta calc__result-cta" href="/contact/?intent=accounting" data-ga="cta_click" data-tb-event="calc_to_quote" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:9px;height:50px;padding:0 22px;border-radius:12px;font-size:15px;font-weight:600;">Book the discovery call</a>
      </div>

      <noscript>
        <div class="calc__noscript">
          <p>The live calculator needs JavaScript. The core rule: <strong>1099-NEC and W-2 are due January 31</strong> of the year after the tax year (rolled to the next business day if that&rsquo;s a weekend); <strong>1099-MISC e-filed to the IRS is due March 31</strong>. Confirm exact dates on IRS.gov, or <a href="/contact/?intent=accounting">book a free discovery call</a>.</p>
        </div>
      </noscript>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- ═══ THE RULES BEHIND IT — federal filing calendar as a v2 .cmp table
    (data-col for mobile stacking) + prose. sand alt band. ═══ -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="deadline-calc-how" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">The rules behind it</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2">The 1099 &amp; W-2 deadlines that matter.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>The federal filing calendar for the most common information returns &mdash; the same rules the calculator applies.</p>
      <p>Any deadline that lands on a Saturday, Sunday, or legal holiday rolls to the next business day &mdash; the calculator applies that roll to the January 31 dates automatically. Send recipient copies and file with the IRS/SSA by the dates shown; e-filing is required once you hit the IRS volume threshold for information returns.</p>
      <p>Late or incorrect filings carry penalties <em>per form</em>, and they scale with how late you are &mdash; which is why clean, current books and accurate contractor records through the year matter more than a last-minute scramble. This page is general information, not tax advice; your CPA files the returns, and we keep the underlying records right.</p>
    </div>
    <table class="cmp" style="margin-top:24px;">
      <caption class="sr-only">Common information-return filing deadlines (federal).</caption>
      <thead><tr><th scope="col">Form</th><th scope="col">To recipient</th><th scope="col">To IRS / SSA</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><th scope="row" data-col="Form"><strong>1099-NEC</strong> <span style="color:var(--color-ink-mute);font-weight:400;">contractor pay</span></th><td class="num" data-col="To recipient">January 31</td><td class="num" data-col="To IRS / SSA"><strong>January 31</strong></td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row" data-col="Form"><strong>W-2</strong> <span style="color:var(--color-ink-mute);font-weight:400;">employee wages</span></th><td class="num" data-col="To recipient">January 31</td><td class="num" data-col="To IRS / SSA"><strong>January 31</strong> (SSA)</td></tr>
        <tr><th scope="row" data-col="Form"><strong>1099-MISC</strong> <span style="color:var(--color-ink-mute);font-weight:400;">rents, other</span></th><td class="num" data-col="To recipient">January 31</td><td class="num" data-col="To IRS / SSA"><strong>Feb 28</strong> paper · <strong>Mar 31</strong> e-file</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

